      <p>The same analyses were repeated controlling for age and lesion size and confirmed the results for the ventral fronto-parietal network seeded from the left MFg (Spearman Rho = .423; <italic>P</italic> = .01), IPs (Rho = .538; <italic>P</italic> = .001), and left opercularis (Rho = .590 ± 0.341; <italic>P</italic> &lt; .001) and corresponded to a reduced performance in category fluency (Fig. <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig5">5</xref>). Additionally, a thinner cortical thickness in the left preSMA functional network (Rho = .439; <italic>P</italic> = .007) and a higher rs-<italic>f</italic>MRI entropy (Rho = −.420 ± 0.370; <italic>P</italic> = .019) in the mid cingulate gyrus functional network were associated with poorer performance in category fluency.</p>
